{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-17T00:11:27.296Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1776384687296_0","parameters":{"file_path":"sdp/verification/t-010@20260416t181925z-verify.md","content":"# Verification Report — T-010@20260416T181925Z\n\n**Verify Agent:** gemini-cli\n**Date:** 2026-04-16\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `src/cypherclaw/render/rules/microtiming.py`\n- `tests/test_microtiming.py`\n- `src/cypherclaw/render/rules/articulation.py`\n- `src/cypherclaw/render/rules/final_rit.py`\n- `src/cypherclaw/render/rules/phrase_arch.py`\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/punctuation.py`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation correctly applies per-role Gaussian jitter:\n- Melodic roles: σ=3.0 ms\n- Ostinato role: σ=1.0 ms\n- Grid-locked roles: σ=0.0 ms (including \"drum\", \"drums\", \"machine\", \"perc\", \"percussion\", \"rhythm\", \"sample\", \"silence\")\n\nJitter is deterministic, using a SHA-256 hash of (step_index, seed) to seed the Box-Muller transform. This ensures reproducibility as required. The `timing_deviation_ms` field is correctly populated on the `Event` objects.\n\n## Completeness\nAll acceptance criteria are met:\n- `microtiming.py` is the only source of timing jitter (white noise) in the `src/` rendering pipeline.\n- σ values are strictly below the 10 ms JND, enforced by a `ValueError` in `__post_init__`.\n- Grid-locked voices emerge with `timing_deviation_ms == 0.0`.\n- Comprehensive tests in `test_microtiming.py` verify distribution σ, role mappings, and deterministic behavior.\n\n## Consistency\nThe rule follows the new `Event`-based contract established in `src/cypherclaw/render/rules/`, consistent with other recent rules like `ArticulationRule` (T-009) and `FinalRitRule` (T-007). While there is an older `score`-based rule set in `my-claw/` (e.g., `PunctuationRule` in T-008), the migration to the new `Event` pipeline is being handled correctly in this task.\n\n## Security\nNo security issues found. Hashing is used for PRNG seeding and does not handle sensitive data. No external dependencies or unsafe operations.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is clean, well-typed, and follows project standards. The use of `hashlib` and `struct` for deterministic seeding is robust. The test suite provides high confidence in the statistical distribution of the jitter.\n\n## Issues Found\n- [ ] [Minor] Some older rules in `my-claw/` (like R6 Punctuation) still use `random.gauss()` for rhythmic durations, but these are distinct from the microtiming jitter pipeline consolidated in T-010.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe implementation is solid. The decision to use a deterministic hash-based jitter source instead of `random.Random` ensures that re-renders are byte-identical even across different rule application orders or partial renderings, which is a significant quality improvement.\n"}}
